report_notes: This is a fundamentally different error class from false_reject claims. The pipeline's category-level keyword matching is correct in identifying these as engine-related components. The problem is that NSA operates at a component-level: each guarantee contract has a specific list of covered parts, and 'Hochdruckpumpe' is not on guarantee 614349's list. Additionally, NSA applies a consequential damage principle â€” if the root cause component (Hochdruckpumpe) is not covered, all resulting damage is also denied. The pipeline has no equivalent logic. This claim highlights the gap between category-level coverage (pipeline) and component-level coverage (NSA).
